blank_1: In this test, a sequence of stimuli is presented on the monitor. The stimuli vary in a range of feature dimensions: color, shape, size and filling. A target stimulus occurs whenever it corresponds in one or the other of two predetermined stimulus dimensions with the preceding stimulus (e.g. the same shape but with different color, size and filling). In order to adapt the difficulty of the task to the performance level of a subject, different levels of difficulty, that is, reactions to "shape" only or to "color or shape", may be selected.

The first condition concerns simple reaction time measurements, in which a cross appears on the monitor at randomly varying intervals and to which the subject should respond as quickly as possible by pressing a key.
